Commentary Text: Mitchell Marsh to Jaiswal, out Caught by Lalit Yadav!! Another dolly of a catch and this time it is Lalit Yadav. Jaiswal has been guilty of too many shuffly movements around the crease and it has ultimately cost him his wicket. He shuffled a long way to the leg-side and Mitchell Marsh spotted it early enough to bowl the bouncer into his body. Cramps him up for room and the mistimed pull goes straight into the bucket hands of Lalit Yadav at deep square. A much-needed breakthrough for the Capitals. Jaiswal c Lalit Yadav b Mitchell Marsh 19(19) [4s-1 6s-1]
